                            <comment id="12975359" author="urandom" created="Mon, 27 Dec 2010 22:24:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Upon further examination...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The null value here is row.cf, it&apos;s null because the read came up empty, so this looks like a race to me (the read is beating the write).  But... the bigger question is, why have we added a read to the write path? This seems very wrong to me.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, what does ReplicateOnWriteTask do that the existing replication doesn&apos;t? How come we&apos;re doing both?  This all seems to have changed as part of the counters implementation, so it would be great if someone involved with that could sound off on this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12975373" author="kelvin" created="Mon, 27 Dec 2010 23:12:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;R-O-W is optional.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The goal is to provide faster convergence for CL.ONE writes.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12975376" author="gdusbabek" created="Mon, 27 Dec 2010 23:25:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12975388" author="urandom" created="Mon, 27 Dec 2010 23:48:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So the NullPointerExceptions are normal?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12975400" author="hudson" created="Tue, 28 Dec 2010 01:10:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Cassandra #642 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra/642/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra/642/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
    set DEFAULT_REPLICATE_ON_WRITE to false. patch by gdusbabek, reviewed by eevans. &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-1903&quot; title=&quot;NullPointerException from o.a.c.db.ReplicateOnWriteTask&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-1903&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-1903&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
